<TEXT>
   Actor Griffin O'Neal is due to appear in
court Friday for allegedly violating his probation by failing to
perform 400 hours of community service.
   The 25-year-old son of actor Ryan O'Neil was ordered to perform
the community service as part of his sentence for a boating accident
that killed a friend, Gian-Carlo Coppola, 23, the son of film
director and producer Francis Ford Coppola.
   O'Neal and Coppola were boating on the South River on Memorial
Day 1986 when their 14-foot runabout struck a towline connecting two
larger vessels. Coppola died of head injuries. O'Neal suffered minor
injuries.
   The two were on a break from filming ``Gardens of Stone'' in
Virginia.
   O'Neal, who was acquitted of manslaughter but convicted on a
negligent boating charge in his 1987 trial, received a 30-day
suspended jail term, 1{ years probation and was ordered to perform
400 hours of community service in California, where he lives.
   Prosecutor Gerald Anders said O'Neal had carried out ``only a
fraction'' of the community service requirement.
   He could face 30 days in jail for probation violation.
