<SECOND>PM-BRF--Bus Crash,0135</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bus Crash Kills 10</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHILPANCINGO, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger bus ran off a highway in
southern Mexico and plunged down a ravine, killing 10 people and
injuring seven, officials said.
   Tomas Hernandez Falma, an officer with the Chilpancingo police
department, said the bus was traveling from Chilapa, 130 miles south
of Mexico City, to the town of Hueycantenango in Guerrero state
before dawn Monday when it crashed into the 150-foot ravine.
   Ten people were killed immediately, Hernandez Falma said.
   The other seven people on the bus were hospitalized in serious
condition, said Javier Gomez, deputy commander of the Red Cross in
Chilpancingo, the state capital.
   The passengers lived in Chilapa and neighboring towns, Hernandez
Falma said, adding that investigators have yet to determine the
cause of the crash.
