<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0452</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dry, Mild Weather Prevails</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Dry, mild weather prevailed across the nation today except for a
dusting of snow in northern Minnesota and rain in the Pacific
Northwest.
   Strong winds and rain swept through Washington and Oregon on
Monday.
   In the Puget Sound area, winds gusted to 62 mph, knocking trees
onto power lines and disrupting service to at least 57,000 customers.
   In Oregon, gusts hit 55 mph along the coast and Astoria received
just over nine-tenths of an inch of rain in the six hours ended at 1
a.m. EST.
   High wind warnings were in effect along the eastern slopes of the
Rockies in Montana and Wyoming. Gusts of 51 mph were recorded at
Cody, Wyo., late Monday and gusts to 80 mph were expected in Montana.
   Dry weather prevailed elsewhere today, with clear skies over much
of the southern two thirds of the country. Fog developed over
eastern sections of Oklahoma and Texas, and south central Texas had
clouds and drizzle.
   Today's forecast called for widespread snow in northwest
Pennsylvania and from western New York state to Vermont and Maine;
lingering snow in northeast Minnesota and western upper Michigan;
strong, gusty winds along the eastern slopes of the northern
Rockies; and fair weather in much of the country.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 20s and 30s from eastern
North Dakota to the upper Mississippi Valley, the Great Lakes and
New England; around 60 across much of the central Plains; the 60s
from Southern California to southern Arizona and from the Gulf Coast
to the southern Atlantic Coast; in the 70s along the Southern
California coast and across central and southern Florida; and in the
40s and 50s elsewhere.
   At 2 a.m. EST, temperatures ranged from 3 degrees below zero at
Craig, Colo., to 72 degrees at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 32 fair; Boston 32 partly cloudy; Buffalo 32
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 45 fair; Cincinnati 32 fair; Cleveland 39
windy; Detroit 35 windy; Miami 67 fair; New York 33 fair;
Philadelphia 28 fair; Pittsburgh 32 fair; Portland, Maine 20 fair;
Washington 31 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 27 cloudy; Chicago 38 windy; Dallas-Fort Worth
34 fair; Denver 31 partly cloudy; Des Moines 34 fair; Indianapolis
35 fair; Kansas City 35 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 26 fair;
Nashville 27 fair; New Orleans 35 fair; St. Louis 40 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 28 fair; Anchorage -1 partly cloudy; Las Vegas
34 fair; Los Angeles 58 fair; Phoenix 45 fair; Salt Lake City 16
fair; San Diego 47 fair; San Francisco 45 partly cloudy; Seattle 45
rain.
   _Canada: Montreal 21 snow; Toronto 32 windy.
