<FIRST>r a PM-WhaleHarassment     01-17 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Whale Harassment,0203</SECOND>
<HEAD>Austrian Tourist Fined For Whale Harassment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Austrian tourist was fined $1,500 after
pleading guilty to harassing whales off Maui.
   ``It seems perfectly clear that he was chasing the whales,'' U.S.
Magistrate Daral Conklin said Monday in issuing the fine for Peter
Gottwald. ``Were he a U.S. citizen, he would spend several nights in
jail.''
   In exchange for the guilty plea, the U.S. attorney's office
dropped its request for a jail sentence.
   U.S. Attorney Dan Bent, who attended the court session, said he
was satisfied with the fine.
   Although federal offices and courts were closed in observance of
Martin Luther King Day, the hearing was held so Gottwald could
return to Austria later in the day.
   Gottwald said he pleaded guilty in order to return home.
   ``This is ridiculous _ the whole situation,'' he said. ``This is
not the aloha spirit.''
   Gottwald and his girlfriend rented a boat on Maui on Jan. 3 and
went to a protected area to get a good look at the whales.
   He says he did not think he was harassing the whales and was not
sure how close he was allowed to get.
</TEXT>
