<HEAD>Fire Stations Cited for Fire Violations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANCHESTER, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state investigator discovered 256 fire
safety problems _ including a lack of smoke detectors and fire
alarms _ in seven Manchester fire stations.
   The investigator from the state fire marshal's office even cited
the city's fire prevention office for hazardous extension cords.
   ``I guess it's embarrassing,'' said Emile Beaulieu, mayor of the
city of 100,000 people.
   The mayor said 115 of the problems have been fixed, but he and
Fire Chief Robert DeCotis said the Fire Department needs more money
to install sprinklers and make other renovations.
   ``We have no money in my budget to take care of major problems,''
DeCotis said. ``I'm complaining right along with everybody else.''
   Last year, one of the Fire Department's oldest stations was
destroyed by fire while its crew was out.
