<HEAD>With PM-Baker Confirmation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   James A. Baker III said today he has been
mislabled by those who ``have described my philosophy as pragmatic.''
   ``I'd like to say that labels can be misleading,'' Baker told the
Senate Foreign Relations Committee as confirmation hearings opened
on his nomination to become the nation's 61st secretary of state.
   ``I am actually a Texas Republican, ALL of whom are
conservative,'' Baker said.
   But he added: ``I will admit to pragmatism, however, if by that
you mean being realistic about the world and appreciating the
importance of getting things done.''
