<DATELINE>WESTWOOD, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   James H. Vaughan, a Christian Brother and
former dean of Iona College, died of a heart attack Friday at
Pascack Valley Hospital. He was 81.
   Vaughan spent his life administering Roman Catholic schools,
serving as principal of Power Memorial Academy in New York City
between 1940 and 1946 and of Leo High School in the late 1940s. He
was dean of Iona College in White Plains, N.Y., from 1955 to 1958.
   Vaughan was superior of the Christian Brothers community at
Bergen Catholic High School in Oradell between 1968 and his
retirement in 1975.
