<HEAD>Lori Savitch, Jessica's Sister, Leaving WTXF-TV</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lori Savitch, younger sister of the late NBC
anchorwoman Jessica Savitch, is leaving the WTXF-TV news department
to join her fiance in West Virginia.
   Ms. Savitch, who joined the station as a reporter in February
1988, tentatively will leave the station April 1. She is planning to
marry Gregory Konat, a molecular biologist who will teach at the
University of West Virginia, on April 15 in Philadelphia. The couple
will live in Morgantown, W.Va.
   ``We feel really confident that we'll be back to Philadelphia
soon,'' said Ms. Savitch, who plans to do free-lance TV or radio
work, or both.
   ``This was a gut-wrenching decision,'' she said. ``This is home
for me, and this is the best job I ever had.''
