<FILEID>AP-NR-01-17-89 1327EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--ChristmasLights     01-17 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Christmas Lights,0120</SECOND>
<HEAD>Still Turned On Because No Money to Pay for Storage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DELANO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Christmas decorations still glow each night
in downtown Delano.
   It's not that residents remain captivated by the holiday; it's
just that the Chamber of Commerce doesn't have enough money to store
the decorations and pay for insurance coverage.
   Because of the lack of funds, the chamber's board voted against
renewing a contract to have a Fresno-area firm store the green and
red decorations. They have been plugged into city lightpoles since
mid-November, so the lights turn on automatically every evening.
   ``It's very embarrassing to me,'' Chamber Manager Dorothy Knight
said on Monday. ``It's bad for the image of the community.''
</TEXT>
