<TEXT>
   Country music singer Randy Travis was
shaken up but not seriously hurt Tuesday when his car went into a
ditch, police and his publicist said.
   Travis, 29, ended up in the ditch after he tried to avoid another
car in rural Cheatham County west of Nashville, publicist Evelyn
Shriver said. Lib Hatcher, Travis' manager, was with him and also
was shaken up, she said.
   They were en route from their farm to a high school to promote a
new booklet on teen-age problems.
   He is honorary chairman of the Youth Yellow Pages, a directory
featuring information and telephone numbers for teen-agers concerned
about AIDS, alcohol, drugs, peer pressure, pregnancy, sexual abuse,
venereal disease and violence.
   Shriver said Travis likely would continue with appearances
Wednesday on the NBC-TV show ``Late Night With David Letterman'' and
Thursday night at the nationally televised Presidential Inaugural
Gala on CBS.
   Travis is known for his hits ``Forever and Ever, Amen'' and his
current ``Deeper Than the Holler.''
