<FIRST>u a AM-SchoolShooting-List     01-17 0435</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-School Shooting-List,0442</SECOND>
<HEAD>A Brief History of Recent School Violence</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-School Shooting</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some recent incidents of school shootings or
hostage-takings:
   OCT. 3, 1988 _ A gunman fires three times into a playground
filled with children at Mascotte Elementary School in Mascotte,
Fla., wounding a 9-year-old girl. The gunman escapes and has not
been captured.
   SEPT. 26, 1988 _ James William Wilson, a 19-year-old man with a
history of psychiatric problems, enters Oakland Elementary School in
Greenwood, S.C. and shoots at students and teachers in the cafeteria
and a third-grade classroom. Two 8-year-old girls are killed and
seven other pupils and two teachers are wounded. Wilson is
apprehended and held for police by a wounded teacher and other
school personnel.
   SEPT. 22, 1988 _ An emotionally disturbed man, Clemie Henderson,
40, shoots to death two men in an auto parts store and wounds a
garbage collector on a street before entering a Chicago school and
killing a custodian. He encounters two police officers called to the
school about an unruly student and shoots both, killing a
policewoman. Her wounded partner shoots and kills Henderson. None of
the school's 150 students are hurt.
   MAY 20, 1988 _ Laurie Dann goes on a rampage at Hubbard Woods
Elementary school in Winnetka, Ill., killing an 8-year-old boy and
wounding five other children. Dann flees to a nearby home where she
wounds one man and shoots herself. Police find Dann also mailed
packages of poisoned food before her shooting spree.
   FEB. 2, 1988 _ A gunman saying he wants to help the homeless
holds dozens of children and teachers hostage in a 12-hour ordeal at
West End Christian School in Tuscaloosa, Ala. Authorities promise
the gunman a pardon and a news conference and overpower him when he
steps out of the school. No one is injured.
   
   MAY 16, 1986 _ A heavily armed couple with a bomb take 150
students and adults hostage at an elementary school in Cokeville,
Wyo. They demand $300 million ransom but are killed when the bomb
explodes accidentally and the man shoots himself. One teacher is
shot in the back as he tries to flee and 74 people suffer
second-degree burns in the blast.
   DEC. 9, 1985 _ A gunman takes six people hostage at Archbishop
Ryan High School in Philadelphia and demands that President Reagan
resign. After a 7{-hour standoff, three of the student hostages
overpower the gunman.
   APRIL 2, 1985 _ An armed man invades an elementary school in
Detroit and holds three children hostage. He releases the children
and surrenders four hours later.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
