<HEAD>Kirov Ballet To Perform in 4 U.S. Cities</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Kirov Ballet from Leningrad, not seen in the
United States for 25 years, will perform in four American cities
next summer, the Metropolitan Opera announced Tuesday.
   The Kirov will dance at the Met from July 3 through 22, then
perform in Washington D.C., San Francisco and a suburb of Los
Angeles. The programs at the Met will include three full-length
ballets, ``Le Corsaire,'' ``Giselle'' and ``Sleeping Beauty,'' as
well as mixed bills.
   The company will appear at Washington's Kennedy Center July 25
through Aug. 6, the War Memorial Opera House in San Francisco Aug. 9
through 16 and the Orange County Performing Arts Center in Costa
Mesa, Calif., Aug. 18 through 27. The company will dance ``Sleeping
Beauty'' and ``Le Corsaire'' in each city, and in Washington and
Costa Mesa it also will dance mixed bills.
   The Kirov Ballet and the Bolshoi Ballet in Moscow are the Soviet
Union's leading and largest companies.
   The Metropolitan Opera also announced that the London Festival
Ballet will perform there from July 25 through Aug. 5, preceded by a
July 18 through 23 engagement at Kennedy Center. In Washington, the
company will dance ``Romeo and Juliet'' and ``La Sylphide.'' In New
York it will dance ``Romeo and Juliet,'' ``Napoli'' and a mixed bill.
