<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Opponents of pornography are commending
action by the Federal Communications Commission in extending to 24
hours a day its ban on indecent communication on radio and TV.
   Larry Braidfoot of the Southern Baptist Christian Life
Commission, the denomination's social action arm, says the FCC
previously had not banned sexually explicit broadcasting on
late-night broadcasts.
   Expansion on Dec. 31 of the ban through all hours ``caps a
struggle which has going on throughout most of the 1980s,''
Braidfoot says.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
