   A Roman Catholic leader says the Soviet release
of a Lithuanian bishop gives ``cautious hope'' of improved
conditions for religion in the Soviet Union.
   Concerning release of Bishop Julijonas Steponavicius from more
than two decades of internal exile and his return to Vilnus,
Lithuania, Monsignor Daniel F. Hoye, general secretary of the U.S.
