   United Methodist leaders, whose denomination has
been losing members for two decades, called at a meeting on
evangelism here for a return to the basics of Bible study, biblical
preaching and winning converts.
   The church needs to get back to the fundamental task of making
``disciples for Jesus Christ,'' said the Rev. John Ed. Mathison,
pastor of the 4,800-member Frazer Memorial United Methodist Church
in Montgomery, Ala., one the fastest growing in the denomination.
