   Economic forecasters had few surprises for
retailers when they told the storeowners that 1988's lackluster
sales would continue in the new year.
   Stuart Robbins, a retail industry analyst with the investment
firm Donaldson Lufkin &amp; Jenrette Securities Corp., said he expected
``more of the same kind of muddling along'' in the economy this
year, resulting in a mediocre retail environment.
