plans to lay off about 2,000 workers, or 5 percent of its worldwide
workforce, to cope with sluggish business.
   The Silicon Valley chip maker also said Monday it would take a
charge against earnings in the current quarter to cover costs of the
dismissals, but said it had not yet decided how big the charge would
be.
