<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 11am,0354</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was down today as traders
continued to take a cautious approach to equities.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was off 10.89 points at
2,213.75 after 1{ hours of trading.
   Declining issues outnumbered advancing ones 3 to 2 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 450 up, 675 down and 572 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 48.44 million shares as of 11
a.m. EST.
   Analysts said traders were focusing on such factors as the level
of the dollar and oil prices, Wednesday's report on the nation's
November trade deficit and Thursday's report on December consumer
prices.
   Also on traders' minds is the outlook for fourth-quarter earnings
at International Business Machines, due Wednesday. Profits are
expected to be up because of good minicomputer sales and gains from
an arbitration award from Fujitsu Ltd.
   Business inventories rose 0.4 percent in November, the Commerce
Department said today.
   The dollar weakened slightly in trading today, giving up some of
its recent gains. Oil futures prices hit a 14-month high on Tuesday
on the New York Mercantile Exchange.
   On the trade front, some analysts are predicting a rise in the
trade deficit to about $11 billion in November from $10.4 billion
the previous month.
   Texas Eastern was up } at 45} on heavy volume. It is being sought
by Coastal for 42 a share, or $2.49 billion. The stock had soared
14} to 45, above the offering price, on Monday.
   Among other actively traded NYSE issues, RJR Nabisco was up ] at
95[, American Telephone &amp; Telegraph was up [ at 29[, and K mart was
up { at 35~.
   In the over-the-counter market, Apple Computer fell 1} to 42. The
personal computer maker said its earnings rose 16 percent and
announced a price cut on some products.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
off 0.30 at 159.48. The American Stock Exchange's market value index
was off 0.42 at 316.39.
