November after seasonal adjustments, the Commerce Department said
today.
   The dollar weakened slightly in trading today, giving up some of
its recent gains. Oil futures prices continued to rise above the
14-month high reached Tuesday on the New York Mercantile Exchange.
   On the trade front, some analysts are predicting a rise in the
trade deficit to about $11 billion in November from $10.4 billion
the previous month.
   Texas Eastern was up 1[ at 46[ on heavy volume. It is being
sought by Coastal for 42 a share, or $2.49 billion. The stock had
soared 14} to 45, above the offering price, on Monday.
   Goodyear sank 2{ to 50|, helping drag down the Dow Jones
industrial average, of which it is a component. The company said it
expects to report fourth-quarter earnings from continuing operations
that are down 53 percent from a year earlier.
   Among other actively traded NYSE issues, RJR Nabisco was up [ at
94~ on heavy volume, American Telephone &amp; Telegraph was unchanged at
29, and Archer Daniels Midland was up | at 21{.
   In the over-the-counter market, Apple Computer fell 1} to 42. The
personal computer maker said its earnings rose 16 percent and
announced a price cut on some products.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
off 0.48 at 159.30. The American Stock Exchange's market value index
was off 0.60 at 316.21.
