<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru   01-17 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0191</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Stocks Close Lower On Profit-Taking</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: updates throughout with close.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices closed lower Tuesday as players took
profits on the market's strong rally in recent weeks.
   Trading volume also was lower amid caution ahead of a string of
economic statistics due out later this week. Key among these is
Wednesday's U.S. trade report for November.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index finished 4.1
points, or 0.2 percent, lower at 1,867.7.
   Volume fell to 424.2 million shares from Monday's 497 million
shares.
   Since the start of the year, the London market has declined in
just three of its 11 trading sessions, and dealers said it was due
for some selling.
   Aside from the U.S. trade report, players also are awaiting news
on British employment and average earnings, due Thursday, and
British inflation figures, scheduled for release on Friday.
   While Monday's news of a slowing in British retail sales in
December was welcomed, the market is hoping the additional reports
will confirm that Britain's interest rate hikes are beginning to
ease inflationary pressures on the economy.
</TEXT>
