<FIRST>r f AM-AutoRecall     01-17 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Auto Recall,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Audi Recalls 35,000 5000 Turbos for Fuel Injector Problems</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Audi of America Inc. on Tuesday recalled about
35,000 1984-88 5000 Turbo and a small number of 1989 Turbo cars
because of a fuel injection system problem that could cause an
engine fire.
   Audi spokesman Joseph Bennett said the company was aware of about
a dozen such fires, resulting in no injuries or accidents.
   The company said in a statement that high temperature and alcohol
in some fuels may harden injector seals, allowing fuel to escape
into the engine compartment and causing a fire.
   Audi will notify owners of affected vehicles during the next
week. Replacement parts will be available beginning early next month
and repairs will be performed free of charge, the statement said.
</TEXT>
