<HEAD>Goodyear Expects Earnings Drop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Goodyear Tire &amp; Rubber Co. on Tuesday
projected a 53 percent decline in its 1988 fourth-quarter earnings
from continuing operations and attributed the anticipated drop to a
soft domestic tire market.
   The company estimated that 1988 fourth-quarter earnings from
continuing operations would be 53 percent lower than the $119.4
million recorded for the same period in 1987.
   A previous company estimate projected earnings for that quarter
at 40 percent to 45 percent lower than the fourth quarter of 1987.
